commit.message:
Sustain all hits, and increase polyphony

This will reduce voice-stealing, which is relevant since
the .sf2 spefifies a long decay time for all samples.

It also changes the synth to treat all notes as sustained
and prevents a user from overriding this.

commit.message:
Update color-maps, prevent bleed

Rather than using a direct math relation-ship
  `color-index-number = MIDI-note - 36`
this allow to map MIDI notes arbitrarily to colors.
This helps when scaling the GUI and map colors are
interpolated between neighbors, and fixes a bug where those
a region between Hi-Hat swish and open hat triggered a tom hit.

It also allows to constrain the visual highlight to a given
kit piece.
